From f4744078b85881b212b84840391cc800f6ecd748 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Keith Calvelli <keith@calvelli.dev>
Date: Wed, 25 Mar 2026 14:26:35 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] fix: share CanvasStore between gateway and channels

The daemon spawns the gateway and channels independently, each creating
their own CanvasStore. When an agent pushes to canvas via a channel
(Telegram, dashboard chat), the frame is stored in the channel's orphan
store, not the gateway's store that WebSocket subscribers watch.

Additionally, Agent::from_config (used by the gateway WebSocket chat)
creates its own orphaned CanvasStore per connection.

Fix: create a single CanvasStore in the daemon and thread it through to
run_gateway, start_channels, and per-connection agents so they all share
the same broadcast.
---
 src/agent/agent.rs  |  8 ++++----
 src/channels/mod.rs |  4 ++--
 src/daemon/mod.rs   | 10 ++++++++--
 src/gateway/mod.rs  |  4 ++--
 src/gateway/ws.rs   |  2 +-
 src/main.rs         | 10 +++++-----
 6 files changed, 22 insertions(+), 16 deletions(-)

